    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A synthetic pigment composed of a double salt of phosphoric acid with manganese and ammonium, first introduced in Germany in 1868 as Nuernberg violet. It has a deep rich violet hue, is lightfast, but has poor hiding power.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
